[{"id":"VR715676","type":"mcq","stimulusHtml":"<div><div class=\"stimulus_reference\"><div class=\"passage\"><div class=\"prose style:1\"><div class=\"standalone_image\"><img alt=\"The figure shows a disk with a fixed pivot on its edge. The center of the disk is indicated, and a circle is drawn to show the path that the disk’s center travels as the disk rotates about the pivot.\" src=\"https://assets.learnosity.com/organisations/578/VR715676.g01.svg\"/></div></div></div></div></div><p class=\"stem_paragraph\">A uniform solid disk can rotate about a fixed pivot point located on its edge, as shown in the figure. The disk has mass <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"m sub D\"><math alttext=\"m sub D\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><msub><mi>m</mi><mtext>D</mtext></msub></math></span></span>, radius <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"r sub D\"><math alttext=\"r sub D\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><msub><mi>r</mi><mtext>D</mtext></msub></math></span></span>, and a rotational inertia about its <span class=\"formatted_text text_decoration:underline\">center</span> of <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"I sub C equals one half m sub D, end sub, r sub D, end sub, squared\"><math alttext=\"I sub C equals one half m sub D, end sub, r sub D, end sub, squared\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mstyle displaystyle=\"true\"><msub><mi>I</mi><mtext>C</mtext></msub><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mn>2</mn></mfrac><msub><mi>m</mi><mtext>D</mtext></msub><msup><msub><mi>r</mi><mtext>D</mtext></msub><mn>2</mn></msup></mstyle></math></span></span>. The disk’s center travels in a circle, also of radius <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"r sub D\"><math alttext=\"r sub D\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><msub><mi>r</mi><mtext>D</mtext></msub></math></span></span>, as the disk rotates about the pivot point with angular speed <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"omega sub 0\"><math alttext=\"omega sub 0\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><msub><mi>ω</mi><mn>0</mn></msub></math></span></span> in the plane of the figure. How does the rotational kinetic energy of the disk compare to the translational kinetic energy of the disk?</p>\n","rubricRef":"VR715676_rubric","choicesHtml":["<p class=\"choice_paragraph\">The rotational kinetic energy is zero.</p>","<p class=\"choice_paragraph\">The rotational kinetic energy is not zero and is less than the translational kinetic energy.</p>","<p class=\"choice_paragraph\">The rotational kinetic energy equals the translational kinetic energy.</p>","<p class=\"choice_paragraph\">The rotational kinetic energy is greater than the translational kinetic energy.</p>"],"answer":3}]